text: Had to recheck the stove three times before leaving. My OCD has been acting up lately. Still managed to have a calm evening with a book. Feeling a bit drained.
Woke up feeling motivated for the first time in weeks. Made a to-do list and actually wanted to tackle it. Had a productive morning before the meeting. Hope it lasts.
Spent the afternoon reorganizing the pantry. Couldn't stop until everything was aligned. OCD tendencies made it take twice as long. At least it looks good now.
Valentine's dinner was nice. Felt energetic and present. Didn't spiral into checking my phone. Small win for today.
Slow morning. Had to wash my hands more than usual. Feeling a bit off but trying not to let OCD dictate the whole day. Made breakfast and took it easy.
Really productive afternoon at work. Finished two reports and felt motivated to start a third. Boss noticed and said good things. Energetic mood carried into the evening.
Exhausted. The need to double-check everything at work drained me. OCD thoughts were loud today. Early night for sure.
Woke up energetic and went for a run. Felt motivated to meal prep for the week. Productive morning before noon. Rare good day.
Afternoon was a blur of tasks. Stayed motivated even when things got tedious. Felt productive crossing items off. No major OCD triggers today.
Evening was rough. Kept re-reading the same email. OCD made it hard to hit send. Finally did it and felt relief.
Lazy morning. Not very productive but okay with it. No strong OCD urges. Just coffee and a slow start.
Productive afternoon. Cleared the backlog and felt motivated to take on more. Energetic enough to go to the gym after. Good day overall.
Stressed about tomorrow. OCD flaring—checked the alarm four times. Trying to breathe and not spiral. Evening tea helped a bit.
Morning errands. Felt energetic and motivated to get things done. Productive trip to the store. Even had time for a walk.
Afternoon meeting went well. Felt productive and motivated to finish the week strong. Energetic vibe in the office. Looking forward to the weekend.
Evening at home. Had to reorder the bookshelf. OCD thing. Once it was done I felt calmer. Weird how that works.
Monday motivation was real. Woke up energetic and got an early start. Productive morning before the chaos. Hope the rest of the week follows.
Spent the afternoon cleaning. Couldn't leave the kitchen until the counters were spotless. OCD took over but the place looks great. Tired now.
Low energy evening. Not very productive. Watched a show and tried to relax. OCD thoughts were quiet which was nice.
Slow but steady morning. Felt motivated to plan the week. Made a list and felt productive. Energetic enough for a short workout.
Really productive afternoon. Knocked out three tasks and felt motivated. Energetic and happy. Best Friday in a while.
Evening was okay. Had to resist the urge to recheck the door. OCD tried to creep in. Took a shower and called it a night.
Monday blues but pushed through. Got motivated after coffee. Productive first half. Energetic enough to keep going after lunch.
Afternoon with friends. Felt energetic and present. No OCD rituals. Just good conversation. Grateful for days like this.
Long day. Felt productive at work but drained by evening. OCD made me re-read a message five times. Need to wind down.
Woke up motivated. Energetic morning routine. Productive before the first meeting. Hope this carries through the day.
Chill afternoon. Not super productive but that's fine. Felt a bit of motivation to tidy up. OCD was manageable.
Evening walk was nice. Felt energetic afterward. Productive in a different way—cleared my head. Motivated for tomorrow.
Friday morning and already motivated. Energetic start. Productive morning. Ready for the weekend.
Productive afternoon. Stayed motivated through the slump. Energetic enough to run errands after work. OCD didn't get in the way.
Tough evening. OCD was loud. Had to redo the routine. Not very productive. Just trying to get to bed.
Good morning. Felt motivated and energetic. Productive morning—cleaned and organized. OCD was mild. Enjoying the day.
Holiday weekend. Relaxed afternoon. Felt motivated to read. Not productive in a work sense but good for the soul. Energetic mood.
Evening at home. Productive in small ways. Motivated to cook. Energetic after dinner. OCD stayed in the background.
Rough morning. OCD made the routine take forever. Not very motivated or productive. Hoping the afternoon is better.
Lazy Sunday afternoon. No pressure to be productive. Felt motivated to call a friend. Energetic conversation. Good reset.
Weekend started. Felt energetic and motivated. Productive in that I finished work on time. OCD was okay. Ready to rest.
New month. Woke up motivated. Energetic morning. Productive start. Trying to keep the momentum. OCD has been quieter this week.
Hot afternoon. Stayed productive in the AC. Motivated to finish the project. Energetic by the end. Felt good.
Monday evening. Tired but okay. Had a productive day. Motivated to keep the week on track. OCD flared a bit before bed.
Slow Sunday morning. Not very productive and that's fine. Felt motivated to do one small thing. Energetic after breakfast. Gentle day.
Productive afternoon. Motivated and energetic. Wrapped up the week well. OCD didn't interfere. Good Friday.
Evening was long. OCD made simple tasks take forever. Not very productive. Hoping tomorrow I feel more motivated and energetic.
Labor Day. Relaxed morning. Felt motivated to do something fun. Energetic and productive in a creative way. No work stress.
Quiet afternoon. Productive in that I rested. Motivated to plan the week. Energetic enough for a walk. OCD was mild.
Evening out. Felt energetic and present. Motivated to be social. Productive in a different sense. Good day.
Friday morning. Motivated to finish the week. Energetic start. Productive before lunch. OCD stayed quiet. Grateful.
Long afternoon. Stayed productive. Motivated by the deadline. Energetic push at the end. OCD tried to distract but managed.
October. Evening at home. Felt motivated to set goals. Productive planning. Energetic about the month ahead. OCD okay.
Monday. Woke up with some motivation. Energetic after coffee. Productive morning. OCD made me double-check a few things but not too bad.
Chill afternoon. Not very productive. Felt a bit motivated to tidy. Energetic after a nap. OCD was manageable.
Evening in. Productive in small ways. Motivated to cook. Energetic and relaxed. No major OCD. Peaceful.
Good morning. Motivated and energetic. Productive start. OCD was mild. Ready for the day.
November. Productive afternoon. Motivated to wrap up tasks. Energetic mood. OCD didn't get in the way. Good start to the month.
Friday evening. Tired but satisfied. Had a productive week. Motivated to rest. Energetic enough for a movie. OCD quiet.
Mid-November. Woke up motivated. Energetic morning. Productive before the weekend. OCD has been better. Hoping it lasts.
Productive afternoon. Motivated to finish before the holiday. Energetic push. OCD made me recheck one thing. Still got it done.
December. Evening at home. Felt motivated to decorate. Productive in a festive way. Energetic and happy. OCD mild.
Cold morning. Slow start. Not very productive. Felt a bit motivated later. Energetic after coffee. OCD okay.
New year. Afternoon planning. Motivated to set intentions. Productive in thinking. Energetic about 2025. OCD has been manageable.
Evening in. Productive day overall. Motivated to keep the momentum. Energetic and calm. OCD didn't take over. Good day.
February. Woke up motivated. Energetic morning. Productive start to the month. OCD was quiet. Hoping for a good month.
Productive afternoon. Motivated and energetic. Got a lot done. OCD tried to creep in but I pushed through. Feeling good.
Long day. Tired. Had a productive day but OCD flared at night. Not very motivated now. Just want to sleep. Tomorrow will be better.
